message.content:
cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on video recognition and classification using audiovisual features.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper introduces a Faster Audio pathway that is integrated with visual counterparts to improve audiovisual perception.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with both audio and visual modalities in the context of video recognition.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper employs DropPathway as a regularization technique to overcome training difficulties arising from different learning dynamics for audio and visual modalities.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper draws inspiration from prior studies in neuroscience to perform hierarchical audiovisual synchronization and improve audiovisual features.
